WEBVTT

00:08.007 --> 00:08.942
Oh, hi, Roz.
Oh, there
you are.

00:08.942 --> 00:10.443
I brought something
for Daphne.

00:11.011 --> 00:13.013
I was just going to leave it
with the doorman.

00:13.013 --> 00:14.414
(sobbing):
Oh...
Oh, Lord.

00:14.414 --> 00:16.349
Did I say something?

00:16.349 --> 00:17.851
Well, actually,
our doorman Morrie

00:17.851 --> 00:19.352
passed away this week.

00:19.352 --> 00:21.354
We just got back
from the funeral.

00:21.354 --> 00:22.355
Oh, my gosh.

00:22.355 --> 00:23.690
I'm so sorry.

00:23.690 --> 00:25.358
Is she going to be all right?

00:25.358 --> 00:27.227
Well, uh, you know, she's been
a little high-strung all week

00:27.227 --> 00:28.728
even before he died.

00:28.728 --> 00:30.997
I guess it's just wedding stuff,
you know.

00:30.997 --> 00:31.765
Yeah.

00:31.765 --> 00:33.666
Ooh...
sorry about that.

00:33.666 --> 00:35.935
So, you brought me something,
Roz?

00:35.935 --> 00:37.437
Well, yeah, I figured
you can't get married

00:37.437 --> 00:39.773
without wearing
something borrowed.

00:39.773 --> 00:42.108
Oh, what a beautiful garter.

00:42.108 --> 00:44.444
Look at all the lovely detail.

00:44.444 --> 00:47.147
I especially like
the little odometer.

00:49.315 --> 00:50.984
(no audio)

00:50.984 --> 00:52.786
Thank you so much, Roz.

00:52.786 --> 00:55.622
Does anybody besides me
feel like a cup of coffee?

00:55.622 --> 00:56.823
Oh, I'll brew a pot.

00:56.823 --> 00:57.590
Oh, don't be silly.

00:57.590 --> 00:58.591
I've been here enough times

00:58.591 --> 00:59.859
to know
how to get the coffee made.

00:59.859 --> 01:02.062
Daphne,
make us some coffee.

01:02.062 --> 01:03.229
Kidding.

01:03.229 --> 01:05.031
(laughing)

01:08.535 --> 01:09.536
"The Wayside Inn."

01:09.536 --> 01:12.038
Is this where you're having
the wedding?

01:12.038 --> 01:13.540
Oh, gosh,
it's just beautiful.

01:13.540 --> 01:14.507
I hope it is.

01:14.507 --> 01:15.975
The planning's
been a nightmare.

01:15.975 --> 01:17.977
I spent an hour today
on the seating chart.

01:17.977 --> 01:19.446
Everyone has
some demand.

01:19.446 --> 01:20.447
"Don't sit me
near the band."

01:20.447 --> 01:21.981
"You mind if I
bring a friend?"

01:21.981 --> 01:23.983
Oh, my God,
you can't seat me next to him.

01:23.983 --> 01:26.252
Exactly. Every selfish,
whiny, little de...

01:26.252 --> 01:29.022
no, you cannot seat me
next to Tim Walsh.

01:29.022 --> 01:31.991
I dated him all last summer
and he dumped me.

01:31.991 --> 01:33.993
He's going with my
bridesmaid, Annie.

01:33.993 --> 01:35.995
I have to seat the
bridesmaids together.

01:35.995 --> 01:37.430
This always happens to me.

01:37.430 --> 01:38.998
Is there no place I can go

01:38.998 --> 01:41.468
without running
into some guy I've dated?

01:41.468 --> 01:43.736
I was reading about
a Trappist monastery
in the Amazon

01:43.736 --> 01:45.939
that they somehow
built into the treetops.

01:45.939 --> 01:48.641
Shut up, you big doily.

01:48.641 --> 01:50.376
This is going
to be awful.

01:50.376 --> 01:51.678
Here I am at a wedding

01:51.678 --> 01:54.214
sitting next to a guy
who dumped me.

01:54.214 --> 01:55.648
FRASIER:
Oh, come on, Roz.

01:55.648 --> 01:57.117
You won't be alone.

01:57.117 --> 01:58.051
You'll be on the arm

01:58.051 --> 02:00.620
of a well-known
Seattle boulevardier

02:00.620 --> 02:01.488
and radio star.

02:01.488 --> 02:02.889
Frasier,
I can't go with you.

02:02.889 --> 02:05.391
I mean... going to a wedding
with your boss

02:05.391 --> 02:07.894
is like going to the prom
with your brother.

02:07.894 --> 02:10.395
Niles and I did not go
to the prom together!

02:11.898 --> 02:14.400
Our dates were sick
and we went stag!

02:20.073 --> 02:22.375
In retrospect, yes,
we should've canceled

02:22.375 --> 02:25.678
the horse-drawn carriage,
but hindsight is 20/20.

